From daa0bb960ab97e638a96e4575bd79c16a3f7e10f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 23:24:55 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] libavcodec: unified -qpfile across
 libx264/libsvtav1/libaom (vmaf-tune)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds an -qpfile <path> AVOption on libx264, libsvtav1, and libaom-av1
that consumes the qpfile format emitted by vmaf-tune's saliency.py
(<frame_idx> <I|P|B> <qp> + per-MB-row deltas).

The new shared parser at libavcodec/qpfile_parser.{c,h} reads the file
once into a VmafTuneQpFile struct so each adapter can map it into its
native ROI / per-block QP-offset API:

  * libx264: forwards the path as qpfile=<path> via x264_param_parse,
    re-using x264's own qpfile reader (per-MB extension since r2390).
  * libsvtav1: SCAFFOLD - parse, log; SVT-AV1 ROI translation deferred.
  * libaom-av1: SCAFFOLD - parse, log; AV1E_SET_ROI_MAP wiring
    deferred (requires per-frame 4-segment quantizer map).

Parser is bounded (NASA POW10), uses strtol + portable fgetc-based
line reader (no POSIX getline dependency, no banned-API per CLAUDE.md
§6), clamps offsets to [-12,+12] matching
tools/vmaf-tune/src/vmaftune/saliency.py.

ADR: docs/adr/0312-ffmpeg-patches-vmaf-tune-integration.md
Research: docs/research/0084-ffmpeg-patch-vmaf-tune-integration-survey.md
---
 libavcodec/Makefile        |   4 +-
 libavcodec/libaomenc.c     |  20 +++
 libavcodec/libsvtav1.c     |  21 +++
 libavcodec/libx264.c       |  18 +++
 libavcodec/qpfile_parser.c | 302 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 libavcodec/qpfile_parser.h |  55 +++++++
 6 files changed, 419 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 libavcodec/qpfile_parser.c
 create mode 100644 libavcodec/qpfile_parser.h

